Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
When I select 'Male' radio button from Page 01 of Pelvic MRI
Then I select any Examination radio button from Page 01 of Pelvic MRI
And I go to Page 3 and select 'Yes' in Contrast enhanced
And I click on 'Sequences' tab and select 'Individual' button
And I select 'DWI' in 'Weighting' dropdown
And I go to Page 05 of Pelvic MRI
And I click on 'Finding' radio button
And dropdown below 'Finding' is enabled

When I select 'Scrotum mass' from the dropdown
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled
And 'I describe' button is preselected

When I select 'I know' button
When I click on 'Charakterization II'
Then 'Signal loss/flow void' checkbox is enabled
And 'Necrosis' checkbox is enabled
And 'Fat' checkbox is enabled
And 'Septations' checkbox is enabled
And 'Fluid level' checkbox is enabled
And 'Cystic changes' checkbox is enabled
And 'Lobulated' checkbox is enabled
And 'Central nidus' checkbox is enabled
And 'Vascular accumulation' checkbox is enabled
And 'Perifocal edema' checkbox is enabled

And 'Strong' radio button is enabled
And 'Low' radio button is enabled
And 'No' radio button is enabled

And 'Washout' checkbox is enabled
And 'Early (arterial) contrast enhancement' checkbox is enabled
And 'Marginal contrast enhancement' checkbox is enabled
And 'Diffusion restriction' checkbox is enabled

And 'Testicles' checkbox is enabled
And 'Epididymis' checkbox is enabled
And 'Tunica albuginea' checkbox is enabled
And 'Tunica vaginalis' checkbox is enabled
And 'Cremaster muscle' checkbox is enabled
And 'Vas deferens' checkbox is enabled

And 'Testicular artery' checkbox is enabled
And 'Pampiniform plexus' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Signal loss/flow void' checkbox
Then 'Diffuse' radio button is enabled
And 'Focal' radio button is enabled
And 'Intratesticular' radio button is enabled
And 'Extratesticular' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Extratesticular' radio button
Then 'Loose body' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Fat' checkbox
Then 'Macroscopic' radio button is enabled
And 'Microscopic' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Septations' checkbox
Then 'Thin' radio button is enabled
And 'Thick' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Strong' radio button
Then 'Homogeneous' radio button is enabled
And 'Heterogeneous' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Low' radio button
Then 'Homogeneous' radio button is enabled
And 'Heterogeneous' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Heterogeneous' radio button
Then 'Nodular parts' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Vas deferens' checkbox
Then 'Right' checkbox is enabled
And 'Left' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Testicular artery' checkbox
Then 'Right' checkbox is enabled
And 'Left' checkbox is enabled

